## ETAPE 1 : CONFIGURER DOCKER DESKTOP (Performance)

### 1.1 Modifier settings.json

Ouvre PowerShell en Admin et ex√©cute :

```powershell
$settingsPath = "$env:APPDATA\Docker\settings.json"
$settings = Get-Content $settingsPath -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json

# Adapter selon ta RAM (ici pour 32GB RAM)
$settings.memoryMiB = 20480    # 20 GB
$settings.cpus = 16            # 16 CPUs
$settings.swapMiB = 4096       # 4 GB swap

$json = $settings | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($settingsPath, $json, [System.Text.UTF8Encoding]::new($false))

Write-Host "Docker settings mis a jour" -ForegroundColor Green
```

### 1.2 Configurer WSL2

```powershell
$wslConfig = @"
[wsl2]
memory=20GB
processors=16
swap=4GB
localhostForwarding=true
"@

$wslConfig | Set-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.wslconfig" -Encoding ASCII
Write-Host ".wslconfig cree" -ForegroundColor Green
```

### 1.3 Red√©marrer Docker

```powershell
wsl --shutdown
```

Puis : Quit Docker Desktop ‚Üí Relancer Docker Desktop

